<hl>
<seg id=1> Gu Yongjiang Says that Inland Economic Development Provides Five Major Opportunities for Hong Kong Special Area </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Gu Yongjiang has indicated that inland economic development provides five major opportunities for Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3>  (-) Long-term. stable prosperity advantageous to Hong Kong's economy. </seg>
<seg id=4> Long-term stable growth of the interior economy will allow Hong Kong's economy to obtain benefits from the interior economy, which is full of vitality. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> (-) Can provide Hong Kong with more business opportunities. </seg>
<seg id=6> As the interior's service industries, such as trade, finance, and retail, are opened up step by step to the outside, Hong Kong's service industry will have more room to develop. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> (-) Advantageous to consolidation of trade and shipping centers in Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=8> In 2010, the total foreign trade of the interior may reach US$100 billion, which will certainly increase the demand for transit and transshipment through Hong Kong and will be advantageous for consolidating the status of Hong Kong as a trade and shipping center. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9>  (-) Further promotes the development of Hong Kong financial markets. </seg>
<seg id=10> As the reform of state-run industries advances, more stock-issuing enterprises will be going abroad to get listed; Hong Kong will be the first choice for state-run industries to obtain foreign listings. </seg>
<seg id=11> This will expand the scope of Hong Kong stock, improve market structure, and promote the development of Hong Kong's bond market.  More Chinese capital will appear in Hong Kong.  All of this will consolidate and reinforce Hong Kong's status as an international financial center. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> (-) Advantageously enhances the international competitive strength of Hong Kong products. </seg>
<seg id=13> Based on the complementary relation between the Hong Kong and inland economies, the strengths of both will be combined, which will enhance the international competitive strength of Hong Kong products. </seg>
</p>
